        "created_at": "2025-05-20T09:36:27.613Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Reporting my experience for anyone coming from search.</p>\n<p>We have some big clusters in production (~4Tbs) and I switched the coordinator list in one shot with no issue to new nodes.</p>\n<p>I got the log that some clients did not have an updated cluster file but they kept working, some of them needed a restart to update their cluster file because theyre cronjobs or they store the fdb file in a kubernetes configmap.</p>",
